ret.doc:
Contains functionality for refining a some query.
The `WixSomeQueryBuilder` functions enable you to run, sort, filter, and control
which results a query returns.

Typically, you build a query using any of the some query functions,
refine the query by chaining `WixSomeQueryBuilder` functions, and then execute the
query by chaining *one* of the following functions: [`find()`](#find), `distinct()`](#distinct), or [`count()`](#count).

For example, the following code queries...:

```javascript
import wixSomeBackend from 'wix-some-backend';

wixSomeBackend.querySome()
    .eq("<property1>", "<value1>")
    .ascending("<property2>")
    .limit(5)
    .find()
    .then( (results) => {
      console.log(results.items);
    } );
```

docs.summary: Cursors to navigate through result pages. Returned if cursor paging was used

members.name: next
members.doc: Cursor pointing to next result page

members.name: prev
members.doc: Cursor pointing to previous result page

docs.summary: Returns the items that match the query.
description: The current page of items retrieved by the query.
The page size is defined by the [`limit()`](wix-some-edm.WixSomeQueryBuilder.html#limit)
function, can be retrieved using the [`pageSize`](#pageSize) property, and
navigating through pages is done with the [`prev()`](#prev) and
When no items match the query, the `items` array is empty.

members.name: count
members.doc: The number of items returned in this response

members.name: offset
members.doc: The offset which was requested. Returned if offset paging was used

members.name: total
members.doc: The total number of items that match the query. Returned if offset paging was used and 'too_many_to_count' flag is not set

members.name: tooManyToCount
members.doc: A flag that indicates the server failed to calculate 'total' field

members.name: cursors
members.doc: Cursors to navigate through result pages. Returned if cursor paging was used
